cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.PL

The paper combines game theory and logical analysis to study the abilities of agents in achieving both quantitative and qualitative objectives in multi-player games. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper proposes a logical framework for reasoning about game states, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of concurrent game models and payoffs also suggests a possible fit for the categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
